# Branch Name Template
#
# Format: <type>/<description>-<base-version>
#
# Types:
#   feature  - New functionality
#   fix      - Bug fixes
#   docs     - Documentation only changes
#   refactor - Code restructuring
#   test     - Test additions or changes
#   chore    - Maintenance tasks
#
# Description:
#   - Use kebab-case (words-separated-by-hyphens)
#   - Keep it concise but descriptive
#   - All lowercase
#   - No special characters or spaces
#
# Base Version:
#   - 7-character short hash of the base commit
#   - Get with: git rev-parse --short HEAD
#   - Shows where branch was created from
#
# Examples:
#   feature/user-authentication-ad87b9f
#   fix/login-timeout-error-b8964e0
#   docs/api-documentation-c7d9e1f
#   refactor/database-queries-d2e3f4g
#   test/integration-coverage-e5f6g7h
#   chore/update-dependencies-f8g9h0i
#
# Bad Examples (don't do these):
#   feature_new_thing         # Use hyphens not underscores
#   FEATURE/SOMETHING        # Use lowercase
#   feature/cool            # Missing base version
#   wip/stuff              # Invalid type
#   feature/my feature      # No spaces allowed
#
# Quick Command:
# BASE=$(git rev-parse --short HEAD)
# git checkout -b <type>/<description>-$BASE

<TYPE>/<DESCRIPTION>-<BASE-VERSION>